..TEXT:
I do not know if it has been observed that
while Dante rightly connects architecture, as the most permanent
expression of the pride of humanity, whether just or unjust, with
the first cornice of Purgatory, he indicates its noble function
by engraving upon it, in perfect sculpture, the stories which
rebuke the errors and purify the purposes of noblest souls.
..TEXT:
<<<FORMATTING-OFF>>>
     ^On the Old Road~, vol. i. sec. 291.
